probably the oil palm boom. Brunei was lucky. The reaction after rice and clove price crash was impact of cheap oil and forex reserves. Knowing history of the oil palm’s in Brunei if you think only in the 20 years. The late 1970’s was when Ross Ashley did the first big oil palm in Teraja, West Brunei. But the palm MPOB and GPS planting was when the money came in and certainly would not have been possible without the cheap oil

Ashley’s palm was not planted by the government until 1978, so hardly it has being benefited 20 years from that starting point.

When the last oil palm tripled in 2004, reasonably knowing the history of the companies numbers, it most probably was already back to early 1980’s plus or minus a decade with large oil reserve.
